			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">How do I become a raid bard?<a name="45383"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 10 04 3:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Question says it.  How do I become a raid bard.  You know, the kind that everyone wishes to be.  I'll admit, I've never been in a guild where we've gone on raids worse than the general for the rogue epic.  Needless to say, I'm becoming dissatisfied always being in super-small guilds (go figure).  
<br />

<br />
For all of my 64 levels I've pretty much soloed for exp, and recently grped in BoT and such.  But now that I'm starting to think about putting myself out on the market for an upper level 60+ guild, I want to hone my raid skills.
<br />

<br />
I guess the bottom line is... how do I do that?  Does anyone know of some good resources where I could read up on such things?</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><img src="http://www.wikmgraphics.com/art/violo_sig_maestro.jpg"></span></td>
