			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How do I become a raid bard?<a name="45424"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 10 04 11:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This site is the best resource for reading about what songs, AAs, and gear you need.  The concert hall is real close (some would say better, not a whole lot of bards use both sites I dont think, but there is definately a commanality between information on both)
<br />

<br />
Notice I didnt say &quot;Learning&quot; how to be a raid bard.  Learning the skills comes with experience.  The best way to &quot;learn&quot; how to become a raiding bard is to RAID!!  Talk to other bards in your guild, be honest and open about your inexperience on raids, they will be more than happy to give you tips.  Every guild uses bards differently, some guilds have more bards then others, your job on 2 raids in the same night may be vastly different.
<br />

<br />
The key thing is HONESTY and observation.  Watch, learn, emulate the bards you see doing things you dont know how to do, or want to know how to do.  
<br />

<br />
Reading threads here will give you a basic foundation of knowledge that you can use to hone your playstyle.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
