			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">A couple ideas<a name="45428"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 11 04 12:17 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, i had the same problem - the first guild I joined with Tangerine was in Elemental planes, and I joined when I was level 65 with about 29 AA.  Needless to say, for about the first month I died a LOT.  Some advice follows:
<br />

<br />
ALWAYS know what boss mob is coming up, if they have an AE, the Range, and the resist needed, whether resistable/curable, etc.
<br />

<br />
NEVER sing AE songs while mobs are being pulled - if you catch agro, FADE
<br />

<br />
Make a fade hotkey - mine looks like this
<br />

<br />
Fade
<br />
/attack off
<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/alt activate 212
<br />
/g FADING - don't heal for a few seconds!
<br />

<br />
Most of what you learn will come with experience, and lots of questions.  Find a nice friendly bard (mine was ledaig  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /> ) who doesn't mind answering a question every 5 minutes, and pick their brain.
<br />

<br />
Investing in Epic/Instrument augments/Instrument items and Instrument augmentation AA (Jamfest 3, Singing mastery 2, Instrument master 3, is a good place to start).
<br />

<br />
Defensive AAs are always a good idea too - you are much more effective with your songs if you are not a corpse <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> .
<br />

<br />

<br />
There are several excellent guides hosted on this website, accessible by clicking on GUIDES at the left side of your screen.  They go into more detail than I do here.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
