			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple ideas<a name="45498"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 11 04 10:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>if you think your versatility is put to the test xp grouping or ldon, then expect it to be far more so in a raid situation.
<br />

<br />
you will be responsible for:
<br />

<br />
pulling
<br />
CCing
<br />
upping the resists of your group/raid
<br />
lowering the resists of the key mobs
<br />
generating maximum DS
<br />
overhasting and/or boosting spell damage for DPS groups
<br />

<br />
and a great deal more...some even truly strange
<br />

<br />
your ability to do these things, like the ability of many other folks in a raid, has a far greater impact and opportunity for mayhem in a raid.  botching one of these tasks has the ability to wipe a raid and the loss in time and the failure of an event is not simply rectified by rezzing folks and doing it again.
<br />

<br />
the returns for this are worth the effort imo
<br />

<br />
bards in raid environment are the glue...learn what holes need to be filled and fill them.
<br />

<br />
its often mob/event specific...ask those in the know what they need most that you can offer and serve it up
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
