			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple ideas<a name="45507"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 11 04 11:31 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One of the most educational things that you can do to learn what is happening on raids is to have your group leader or, better yet, the raid leader gain the &quot;Health of Target's Target&quot; Leadership AA.  I am the raid leader for our guild and it was the first thing I bought, at a hefty 9 AAs.  But the thing about this is, whatever you have targeted you have a little window that shows you what IT is targeted on.  You start to notice some interesting things.  Bard song agro is low -- we all know that.  But I think people do not realize how large AOE song agro really is.  I was pulling in GoD last night for my guild and one pull, the other bard in our 40 person raid had Chorus of Marr still up on the pull.  I tagged a mob with Harmony of Sound, slowed it with Requeim of Time on the pull, and the INSTANT the mob moved into AOE range he changed targets to the other bard.  Now the main tank had no problem taking agro away in a split second, but that tells you something right there -- AOE agro overwrites puller agro very easily.  That is probably lesson number one on being a raid bard.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443370">Steppy Astravox</a><br>
