			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple ideas<a name="45831"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 14 04 7:21 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Some great advice, particularly the general raiding stuff, and not singing on inc.
<br />

<br />
One other thing to do is re-learn some of your songs. When grouping I very rarely use some songs but on raids they become much more important.
<br />

<br />
<b>Songs</b>:
<br />
Charisma song boosts the chance for DI to trigger on the MT. Ask the clerics/MT if they are using DI, and if the MTs cha is below about 250 its probably worth singing charisma. Mainly used on mobs with high or very spiky DPS.
<br />

<br />
Nivs harmonic - AC boost. Rarely used in xp groups, boosting up the MTs AC can give significant benefits to the raid.
<br />

<br />
AE resists vs group resists. Elemental and Purifying chorus are good AE resist songs, but range is limited (esp without EN AAs). Learn its range and learn to cover the key players. Sometimes this is the MT, more often it'll be the clerics. Know the spells you are up against, know their resists, and work out if AE resist songs will actually be enough to help. Also consider using group resists as well - it'll overwrite the AE song for your group but give a significant extra boost
<br />

<br />
DS: Against unslowable or slow-mitigating mobs your DS can add far more DPS than anything else you'll do. Learn to get the most out of it (amp+vots or puretone for example) and don't forget zek too.
<br />

<br />
Highsun, lull, mezz, snare, fade - Familiar tools I am sure. But try pulling with a monk partner and learn to use your tools alongside their ones. 
<br />

<br />
<b>Gear</b>
<br />
Two things you can get to really help as a raiding bard:
<br />

<br />
1) VotS from Ssra basement, soloable at 64-65, though easier with a partner. Boosts singing by 0.6
<br />
2) Epic, boosts all songs by 0.8 (1.8 mod)
<br />

<br />
You say your guild is too small to get your epic, and its sure not easy to get Trak down, but do what you can. If you're joining a raiding guild then chances are a single group can kill Trak with you at some stage, so make sure you've got everything else you can get with your friends. Similarly - PoFear is one-groupable (or soloable if you don't mind risks!) and Phinny is a joke I'm sure you can solo her yourself.
<br />

<br />
<b>Groups</b>
<br />
A bard's strength is that they augment the strength's of their group members. Mana regen, overhaste, DoT and nuke focus, AC, stats etc. Try to arrange to get in a group where you will do most benefit. You're not going to add much to a shaman or enchanter, but get in a group with a bunch of wizards and rangers and they'll appreciate it. Or go for melees, rogues and monks will love the overhaste and atk boost. Or group with the MT for cha, AC and massive DS.
<br />

<br />
Above all though, raid, listen, learn and have fun!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
