				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple ideas<a name="45873"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 14 04 11:29 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Snare song would be Largos Absonant Binding(51), fade is referring to Fading Memories AA. Snare song has limited use in higher raid content, it doesnt last long enough to help charmers with pets, it doesnt draw enough aggro to successfuly pull mobs out of the raid to kite, and it won't land on most planar bosses. Ranger/druid snare has much more use than our song.
<br />

<br />
In my opinion, a lot of what you will be required to do on raids is very much limited by how many bards in your guild actively raid. Our guild recently recruited 3 bards where we only had 3 before. With fewer bards, more raid wide demands will be placed on you such as AE resists and AE mana which require some tactics(know when to stop singing! Especially on pulls!). 
<br />

<br />
With more bards, you start to specialize forming DPS groups(bard sings haste/atk maxing songs) Caster groups(bard sings focus/mana maxing songs) and other groups that focus on one facet of the raid.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
