				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple ideas<a name="45875"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 14 04 11:32 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For me the Never have songs up rule is ONLY for AEs. Singing a group buff on 5 other people draws negligent aggro. However, singing AE regen on a 72 person raid will get you smooshed if you do so before MA establishes aggro. PoV is something you definitely should keep up if resists are important.
<br />

<br />
Also, the fact is you CAN keep AE songs up just do not pulse it before the MA establishes aggro. MAs generally wont take more than 3 ticks to generate enough aggro that you wont get squished from AE songs. My tactic if Im doing anything AE is, keep song up until puller calls inc, tap song off, when ma calls assist tap song on, in most cases the AE effect wont wear off.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
