			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple ideas<a name="45957"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 14 04 4:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Additionally, since you stated that you mostly soloed up to 64th, try forming outside of the box exp groups.  Experiment with your song line up.  Try to see what kind of difference it makes against the mobs you are fighting, ie, mobs die faster, group takes less damage, healers heal less, casters have more mana, and so on.  It's knowing/using song/situation nuances to greater advantage that makes for a greater bard.
<br />

<br />
It isn't always about what you do during fights but what you do before and after.  During the fights is important for sure, but no more so than before and after.  Being aware of what is going on around you is vital for any great bard.  Situational holes can open up at any time during a raid.  It's the attention to detail and surroundings that can make the difference, avoiding potential additional down time or worse, a wipe.  It's being able to see something that isn't right combined with the ability to help fix it that can make or break raids.  Granted it isn't just a bard that can do this.  All the classes can to one extent or another.
<br />

<br />
The biggest aspect of everything posted so far would to be listening.  Listening is more important than stopping aoe songs, cause in general listening will give you the information to know if you should stop songs or not. For instance:
<br />

<br />
I was at a raid last night doing RD in HoH.  The MT of the group was constantly sending me tells about what to do and not do.  How it was important to hit him with resists immediately, yet not gain agro from doing so.  I already knew all of this, but listened anyway, just in case there was something I didn't know.  At the end of the fight my group was all full health.  Yet, looking down at corpses I knew right off who it was that was singing aoe mana song when RD popped.
<br />

<br />
Polara Magami</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
