			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple ideas<a name="46764"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 17 04 5:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>going to enforce the dont sing ae songs on inc, or when pullers are trying to work on a pull.  If they get in range, thats a nasty train.  But dont worry if it happens to you, it's something we all learn the hard way.
<br />

<br />
Try to get in a group that will be best suited for you at the raid, mostly if you have just yourself as the only bard, get in a group with warriors and clerics, and help them as much as possible, as well as keep your ae's up.
<br />

<br />
Generally, you can see yourself in a few different group make ups, with tanks Niv's harmonic is a godsend, as well as Zek/PoV and Cha if you see mobs with a lot of spikey dps or able to one round 10k tanks, makes having DI going off that much easier.
<br />

<br />
If you are on a very heavy MR fight, and when the boss has an MR debuff to it, toss in Guardian Rythems.  It stacks with PoV and can help out with mobs with -mr effects and mr based ae's(TZ in Time for example). Or toss it in if the general raid population hasnt maxed out resists yet.
<br />

<br />
DPS Ranged groups like wizzys and rangers like to have rizlona's up all the time along with marr.  Melee groups like to have atk buffs/str/hate mostly, so you can find your self meleeing with them if you have a pure melee group.
<br />

<br />
Try to not get on rampage.  It's tough, because when the RT goes down I normally end up on rampage.  Make a hotkey to say you are on rampage as well send a few tells to some of your healers to start healing you.  Stop all attacking, but continue songs.  Druids can heal bards on ramp, but they have a harder time if you are eating ripostes.  If you get low on hp, and your job is essential, fade and get out of the way and send tells for a heal.  
<br />

<br />
Make sure you know who you can send tells to ahead of time, people on rots have a hard time sometimes getting someone healed then people who are assist healing.
<br />

<br />
Buffs, always send tells for buffs if you missed an mgb or would like one that isnt on the list of stuff to be mgb'd.  Shouting, /rsay, and /gu asking for buffs is unneeded spam.
<br />

<br />
Ask questions if you dont know what to do.  Each guild can and will use their bards differently.  Some will use you for pulling, thus learning to pull would be a good idea.  Others will let you hang out with the raid and do your stuff.
<br />

<br />
Learn quick targetting, cycle your npc targets often.  Help the chanters with mezzing on a train.  find one thats moving and mez it.  Get access to your chanter channel and call out your mezzes(and ask them to assist to remez), if your chanters are smart, they will assist off you asap and cast a mez on that mob to lock it down so you can get back to whatever else.
<br />

<br />
If you are pulling, keep Highsun, lull, mez, da, deftdance, and fade at your finger tips, they are very good pulling tools
<br />

<br />
Use puretone on all boss fights, this will increase quite a bit of things.
<br />

<br />
And lastly, if you find yourself in a spot in the raid where you cant get into a group you want, and there is nothing you can do to help your group or if you feel like messing around on a trivial encounter,  Load your favorite drum, dots, and nukes, and dps away, </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
