				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple ideas<a name="47380"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 21 04 2:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>best to attempt to max your singing mods asap as well, SM3, ISM, AT3 and Echo3 as well.  
<br />

<br />
Btw with tests, and I'm sure everyone here has tested this, puretone will give a 2.8 instrument mod that doesnt stack with your current worn instrument mod.  So it doesnt matter if you wield anything or not to give a singing mod(Or instrument mod at that) while puretone is active, you will be given a 2.8 mod as if you had a 2.8 instrument equiped, even if you have no instrument equiped.
<br />

<br />
But, you can still get pretty high up in singing mods without puretone.
<br />

<br />
Stick from Keeper of Sorrows, or Tribal Mask(2.0)+Amp(1.0)+VoTS(0.6)+SM3(0.6)+ISM(0.2)=4.4, you'll need to get Echo3 to get a mod like that(Through testing, I think we got up to 4.5 with echo3), so all the shei cloak will do is add another 0.1 to your mod.
<br />

<br />
So puretoning will not really do much, shei wont either, even anything over 2.1 wont really add anymore to your mod.  But they are all convience mostly.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
