				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
Couple things about AE songs on raids...
<br />

<br />
They can be played safely if you are smart about it.
<br />
Things to keep in mind...
<br />
1.) Target of Target rules watch this if you pulse is off you will get argo.. if you see your name pop up Fade
<br />

<br />
2.) Remember songs last 3 tics (18 sec).. yes we all know this but it doesn't mean that we have to leave Marr on auto pilot all the time.. only sing it every 18 secs when a puller is fetching.  This way it is up and your chances of pulling argo is greatly reduced!  
<br />

<br />
3.) This is a hard one... know the ranges of your songs.   Have people test it for you often... different zones give the appearance of a larger or smaller radius.  Try to get use to it.  This will help you a lot with tip #2.
<br />

<br />
4.) This goes without saying know your target.  Some mobs you can take a hit or 2 from... and its ok to get argo for a split second.  Some will kill you and your raid...  if you do not know ASK!
<br />

<br />
5.) We all know FM is your best friend.  We also know AE songs draw HUGE amounts of argo.  Know your MT and what you can get away with... comes with time and death.  Not all MTs are the same.  If you are full mana at a start of a fight.  Try fading 1-2 times during the fight just to make sure you do not get argo.  I like to pop it off either when the mob is at 99 or 98 (to keep me off rampage and make sure I dont' mes with MTs argo).  Another good time is around 75% and 30%.
<br />

<br />
6.) In my opinion the #1 killer of melee bards is enrage/rampage WATCH FOR IT! 9 out of 10 times the reason I die is because of enrage... it is ok to turn off melee our dps sucks anyways and will not be missed that much.
<br />

<br />
7.) Always have Deftdance hotkeyed AE songs can help with bad pulls when a FEW to many mobs are inc.  The all come to kill you you deftdance... mes and let the changers do their work.. can help. Assuming you don't die first... FM if you must.
<br />

<br />
8.) Anyways this is long enough... you get the idea.  There is lots of stuff to learn.  GET YOUR DEFENSE AAs, FM, IM... nuff said....
<br />

<br />
Have fun</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
